Working through feelings helps us move forward, but sometimes we don’t even know what we feel; sadness because prom is canceled, or anxiety because you can’t see your friends? A great way to get in touch with your feelings is to journal. As you do, remember:
• Be kind to yourself.
• Everything you’re feeling is okay.
• Don’t judge yourself.
#WellnessWednesday #Whathelpsus #asd20 #inthistogether #doingmypartCO

• Plan a virtual study group/session.

shared_text:
Chinook Trail Elementary
April 9 at 6:48 PM ·

post_text:
Remember eLearning looks different from child-to-child. The goal is to have ongoing, meaningful activities that support learning. That could mean reading a story and talking about lessons learned, heading into the back yard to collect insects for a science lesson or logging onto a learning management system to do an algebra assignment. Be sure to keep working closely with your child's teacher to make learning work for you and let us know if you have questions.

Here is a pic, submitted by our families, of neighborhood students learning together this morning. These families are doing their best to safely work together to make the best of a challenging situation. #asd20 #doingmypartCO

post_text:
Notice of Public Hearing for Academy District 20

Pursuant to C.R.S. 22-2-117 (1)(a), Academy District 20 (ASD20) is requesting a waiver from the State Board of Education from C.R.S. 22-30.5-107 (1)(b) regarding the deadline for filing a charter school application. ASD20 desires to change the charter school application filing deadline from Oct. 1, to April 15, for a charter applicant to be eligible for consideration for opening in the following calendar year.

The ASD20 Board of Education will consider the waiver request at a public hearing on March 6, 2020, 4 p.m., at the Academy District 20 Education and Administration Building, 1110 Chapel Hills Drive, Colorado Springs, Colo., 80920.

Public comment will be welcome during this hearing.
text:
Notice of Public Hearing for Academy District 20

Pursuant to C.R.S. 22-2-117 (1)(a), Academy District 20 (ASD20) is requesting a waiver from the State Board of Education from C.R.S. 22-30.5-107 (1)(b) regarding the deadline for filing a charter school application. ASD20 desires to change the charter school application filing deadline from Oct. 1, to April 15, for a charter applicant to be eligible for consideration for opening in the following calendar year.

The ASD20 Board of Education will consider the waiver request at a public hearing on March 6, 2020, 4 p.m., at the Academy District 20 Education and Administration Building, 1110 Chapel Hills Drive, Colorado Springs, Colo., 80920.

Public comment will be welcome during this hearing.

post_text:
We need your help! The Gazette is doing a story today about how snow days and closure impact families of school-aged children. That said, they are hoping to hear from you.

If you are able and willing, please answer the following question below. They may use your quote in the story. Be sure to state if you are a parent, grandparent, etc., and how let them know how many students you have in our district and even what school they attend (but that is optional).

Question: "What impact do weather related school delays and closures have on you as a parent or family member?"

Thanks in advance - we have the best families!
